<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,335,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">PHYLLODON</emphasis>
Schimp.
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1395,1563]" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">
Five species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schimper" authorityYear="1851" box="[312,427,1395,1421]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[312,427,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">Phyllodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been known in 
<collectingCountry box="[668,739,1395,1421]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
: they are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. E. A. S. Camara" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Dixon" box="[847,979,1395,1421]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="bilobatus">
<emphasis box="[847,979,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. bilobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. E. A. S. Camara" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Bosch &amp; Sande Lac." box="[994,1138,1395,1421]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="glossoides">
<emphasis box="[994,1138,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. glossoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Cardot" box="[1153,1292,1395,1421]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="lingulatus">
<emphasis box="[1153,1292,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. lingulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mitt.) J. T. Wynns (2020: 647)" authorityName="J. T. Wynns" authorityPageNumber="647" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Mitt." class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="laevifolius">
<emphasis box="[1307,1452,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. laevifolius</emphasis>
(Mitt.) J.T. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wynns, J. T." box="[262,477,1431,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" pagination="633 - 656" refId="ref9928" refString="Wynns, J. T. (2020) New names and new combinations for hypnalean mosses. The Bryologist 123 (4): 633 - 656. https: // doi. org / 10.1639 / 0007 - 2745 - 122.4.633" type="journal article" year="2020">Wynns (2020: 647)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bosch &amp; Sande Lac.) S. He" authorityName="S. He" baseAuthorityName="Bosch &amp; Sande Lac." box="[531,973,1431,1457]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="similans">
<emphasis box="[531,651,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. similans</emphasis>
(Bosch &amp; Sande Lac.) S. He
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="He, S. &amp; Nguyen, K. S." box="[1007,1290,1431,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" pagination="32 - 88" refId="ref8494" refString="He, S. &amp; Nguyen, K. S. (2012) New records and an updated checklist of the mosses of Vietnam. Tropical Bryology 34: 32 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / bde. 34.1.5" type="journal article" year="2012">He &amp; Nguyen (2012: 59)</bibRefCitation>
. In the present study, only one species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Cardot" box="[392,530,1466,1492]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="lingulatus">
<emphasis box="[392,530,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">P. lingulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed, whereas other four species records are interpreted as misidentification and should be excluded from moss flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[640,711,1501,1527]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
. For details, see the section “Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Fleischer (1923:" authorityYear="1351" box="[1176,1341,1501,1527]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="1" pageNumber="226" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1341,1501,1527]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">Glossadelphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
excluded from moss flora of 
<collectingCountry box="[352,422,1536,1562]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="226">China</collectingCountry>
” below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
